    {"id": "GS070", "section": "General Science", "topic": "Moon Phases", "question_text": "A lunar eclipse occurs when:", "options": ["The Moon passes between Earth and the Sun", "Earth passes between the Sun and Moon, casting a shadow on the Moon", "The Moon is at its closest point to Earth", "The Sun's light reflects off Earth onto the Moon"], "correct_index": 1, "difficulty": 2, "explanation": "A lunar eclipse occurs when Earth passes directly between the Sun and Moon, casting Earth's shadow onto the Moon. A solar eclipse occurs when the Moon passes between Earth and the Sun.", "test_types": ["ASVAB"]},

